               <p>THOMAS WHITNEY. I am an officer. On the 18th of July, about half past one o'clock, I was at the corner of Union-street, Hackney-road; I saw the prisoners, with another person, attempting to pick a gentleman's pocket; I followed them, and at the corner of <placeName id="t18310908-320-crimeloc1647">Union-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-320-crimeloc1647" type="placeName" value="Union-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-320-crimeloc1647" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-320-off1645 t18310908-320-crimeloc1647"></join> I saw Daley go deliberately behind a young woman, and unclasp the necklace from the child's neck, which she had - I seized the prisoners, but they had passed the necklace to the third person, who ran off with it; he was younger than them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-320-person2312">
                  EMMA 
                  BEDFORD
